{
  "video_id": "rpJx5VLQMxk",
  "title": "What to trust in a \"post-truth\" world | Alex Edmans",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13675.0,
      "end_time": 16595.0,
      "text": "Belle Gibson was a happy young Australian."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16619.0,
      "end_time": 19642.0,
      "text": "She lived in Perth, and she loved skateboarding."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20173.0,
      "end_time": 24622.0,
      "text": "But in 2009, Belle learned that she had brain cancer and four months to live."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 25340.0,
      "end_time": 28567.0,
      "text": "Two months of chemo and radiotherapy had no effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 29145.0,
      "end_time": 30645.0,
      "text": "But Belle was determined."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 30669.0,
      "end_time": 32799.0,
      "text": "She&#39;d been a fighter her whole life."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 32823.0,
      "end_time": 36117.0,
      "text": "From age six, she had to cook for her brother, who had autism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36141.0,
      "end_time": 38529.0,
      "text": "and her mother, who had multiple sclerosis."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38553.0,
      "end_time": 40306.0,
      "text": "Her father was out of the picture."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40736.0,
      "end_time": 44220.0,
      "text": "So Belle fought, with exercise, with meditation"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44460.0,
      "end_time": 46885.0,
      "text": "and by ditching meat for fruit and vegetables."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 47387.0,
      "end_time": 49587.0,
      "text": "And she made a complete recovery."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50784.0,
      "end_time": 52363.0,
      "text": "Belle&#39;s story went viral."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 52387.0,
      "end_time": 55780.0,
      "text": "It was tweeted, blogged about, shared and reached millions of people."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 56246.0,
      "end_time": 59357.0,
      "text": "It showed the benefits of shunning traditional medicine"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 59381.0,
      "end_time": 60848.0,
      "text": "for diet and exercise."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 61381.0,
      "end_time": 65879.0,
      "text": "In August 2013, Belle launched a healthy eating app,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65903.0,
      "end_time": 67252.0,
      "text": "The Whole Pantry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67276.0,
      "end_time": 71298.0,
      "text": "downloaded 200,000 times in the first month."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 73228.0,
      "end_time": 76270.0,
      "text": "But Belle&#39;s story was a lie."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 77227.0,
      "end_time": 78761.0,
      "text": "Belle never had cancer."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 79601.0,
      "end_time": 83734.0,
      "text": "People shared her story without ever checking if it was true."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 84815.0,
      "end_time": 88350.0,
      "text": "This is a classic example of confirmation bias."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 88403.0,
      "end_time": 93790.0,
      "text": "We accept a story uncritically if it confirms what we&#39;d like to be true."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 93484.0,
      "end_time": 95990.0,
      "text": "And we reject any story that contradicts it."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 96937.0,
      "end_time": 98762.0,
      "text": "How often do we see this"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 98786.0,
      "end_time": 101831.0,
      "text": "in the stories that we share and we ignore?"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 101855.0,
      "end_time": 106370.0,
      "text": "In politics, in business, in health advice."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 107180.0,
      "end_time": 111286.0,
      "text": "The Oxford Dictionary&#39;s word of 2016 was \"post-truth.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 111768.0,
      "end_time": 115260.0,
      "text": "And the recognition that we now live in a post-truth world"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 115284.0,
      "end_time": 118648.0,
      "text": "has led to a much needed emphasis on checking the facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 119339.0,
      "end_time": 120736.0,
      "text": "But the punch line of my talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 120760.0,
      "end_time": 123751.0,
      "text": "is that just checking the facts is not enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 124347.0,
      "end_time": 127274.0,
      "text": "Even if Belle&#39;s story were true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 127298.0,
      "end_time": 129365.0,
      "text": "it would be just as irrelevant."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 130457.0,
      "end_time": 131607.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 131957.0,
      "end_time": 135465.0,
      "text": "Well, let&#39;s look at one of the most fundamental techniques in statistics."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 135489.0,
      "end_time": 137899.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s called Bayesian inference."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 138251.0,
      "end_time": 141187.0,
      "text": "And the very simple version is this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 141211.0,
      "end_time": 144479.0,
      "text": "We care about \"does the data support the theory?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 145530.0,
      "end_time": 148509.0,
      "text": "Does the data increase our belief that the theory is true?"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 149520.0,
      "end_time": 153903.0,
      "text": "But instead, we end up asking, \"Is the data consistent with the theory?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 154838.0,
      "end_time": 157352.0,
      "text": "But being consistent with the theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 157377.0,
      "end_time": 160306.0,
      "text": "does not mean that the data supports the theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 160799.0,
      "end_time": 161958.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 161982.0,
      "end_time": 165807.0,
      "text": "Because of a crucial but forgotten third term --"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 165831.0,
      "end_time": 169388.0,
      "text": "the data could also be consistent with rival theories."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 169918.0,
      "end_time": 174585.0,
      "text": "But due to confirmation bias, we never consider the rival theories,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 174609.0,
      "end_time": 177760.0,
      "text": "because we&#39;re so protective of our own pet theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 178688.0,
      "end_time": 181101.0,
      "text": "Now, let&#39;s look at this for Belle&#39;s story."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 181125.0,
      "end_time": 185339.0,
      "text": "Well, we care about: Does Belle&#39;s story support the theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 185363.0,
      "end_time": 186966.0,
      "text": "that diet cures cancer?"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 186990.0,
      "end_time": 188777.0,
      "text": "But instead, we end up asking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 188801.0,
      "end_time": 192845.0,
      "text": "\"Is Belle&#39;s story consistent with diet curing cancer?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 193790.0,
      "end_time": 195394.0,
      "text": "And the answer is yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 195839.0,
      "end_time": 199942.0,
      "text": "If diet did cure cancer, we&#39;d see stories like Belle&#39;s."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 200839.0,
      "end_time": 203688.0,
      "text": "But even if diet did not cure cancer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 203712.0,
      "end_time": 206355.0,
      "text": "we&#39;d still see stories like Belle&#39;s."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 206744.0,
      "end_time": 211934.0,
      "text": "A single story in which a patient apparently self-cured"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 211958.0,
      "end_time": 215132.0,
      "text": "just due to being misdiagnosed in the first place."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 215680.0,
      "end_time": 219600.0,
      "text": "Just like, even if smoking was bad for your health,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 219300.0,
      "end_time": 222334.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d still see one smoker who lived until 100."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 222664.0,
      "end_time": 223814.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 224157.0,
      "end_time": 226719.0,
      "text": "Just like, even if education was good for your income,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 226743.0,
      "end_time": 231240.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d still see one multimillionaire who didn&#39;t go to university."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 231480.0,
      "end_time": 236320.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 236560.0,
      "end_time": 239967.0,
      "text": "So the biggest problem with Belle&#39;s story is not that it was false."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 239991.0,
      "end_time": 242522.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s that it&#39;s only one story."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 243940.0,
      "end_time": 247475.0,
      "text": "There might be thousands of other stories where diet alone failed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 247499.0,
      "end_time": 249433.0,
      "text": "but we never hear about them."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 250141.0,
      "end_time": 254360.0,
      "text": "We share the outlier cases because they are new,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 254610.0,
      "end_time": 255928.0,
      "text": "and therefore they are news."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 256656.0,
      "end_time": 259132.0,
      "text": "We never share the ordinary cases."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 259156.0,
      "end_time": 262370.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re too ordinary, they&#39;re what normally happens."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 263125.0,
      "end_time": 266220.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the true 99 percent that we ignore."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 266244.0,
      "end_time": 269212.0,
      "text": "Just like in society, you can&#39;t just listen to the one percent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 269236.0,
      "end_time": 270394.0,
      "text": "the outliers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 270418.0,
      "end_time": 273840.0,
      "text": "and ignore the 99 percent, the ordinary."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 274220.0,
      "end_time": 277276.0,
      "text": "Because that&#39;s the second example of confirmation bias."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 277300.0,
      "end_time": 280690.0,
      "text": "We accept a fact as data."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 281380.0,
      "end_time": 285600.0,
      "text": "The biggest problem is not that we live in a post-truth world;"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 285300.0,
      "end_time": 288799.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s that we live in a post-data world."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 289792.0,
      "end_time": 293536.0,
      "text": "We prefer a single story to tons of data."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 294752.0,
      "end_time": 297768.0,
      "text": "Now, stories are powerful, they&#39;re vivid, they bring it to life."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 297792.0,
      "end_time": 300130.0,
      "text": "They tell you to start every talk with a story."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 300380.0,
      "end_time": 301188.0,
      "text": "I did."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 301696.0,
      "end_time": 306450.0,
      "text": "But a single story is meaningless and misleading"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 306474.0,
      "end_time": 309323.0,
      "text": "unless it&#39;s backed up by large-scale data."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 311236.0,
      "end_time": 313593.0,
      "text": "But even if we had large-scale data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 313617.0,
      "end_time": 315775.0,
      "text": "that might still not be enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 316260.0,
      "end_time": 319397.0,
      "text": "Because it could still be consistent with rival theories."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 320136.0,
      "end_time": 321286.0,
      "text": "Let me explain."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 322720.0,
      "end_time": 325334.0,
      "text": "A classic study by psychologist Peter Wason"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 325358.0,
      "end_time": 327310.0,
      "text": "gives you a set of three numbers"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 327334.0,
      "end_time": 330239.0,
      "text": "and asks you to think of the rule that generated them."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 330585.0,
      "end_time": 335610.0,
      "text": "So if you&#39;re given two, four, six,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 335850.0,
      "end_time": 336234.0,
      "text": "what&#39;s the rule?"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 336895.0,
      "end_time": 340114.0,
      "text": "Well, most people would think, it&#39;s successive even numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 340767.0,
      "end_time": 342282.0,
      "text": "How would you test it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 342306.0,
      "end_time": 345568.0,
      "text": "Well, you&#39;d propose other sets of successive even numbers:"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 345592.0,
      "end_time": 348909.0,
      "text": "4, 6, 8 or 12, 14, 16."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 349546.0,
      "end_time": 352346.0,
      "text": "And Peter would say these sets also work."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 353124.0,
      "end_time": 355688.0,
      "text": "But knowing that these sets also work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 355712.0,
      "end_time": 360477.0,
      "text": "knowing that perhaps hundreds of sets of successive even numbers also work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 360501.0,
      "end_time": 361849.0,
      "text": "tells you nothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 362572.0,
      "end_time": 365930.0,
      "text": "Because this is still consistent with rival theories."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 366889.0,
      "end_time": 370940.0,
      "text": "Perhaps the rule is any three even numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 371000.0,
      "end_time": 373133.0,
      "text": "Or any three increasing numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 374365.0,
      "end_time": 377253.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the third example of confirmation bias:"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 377277.0,
      "end_time": 380966.0,
      "text": "accepting data as evidence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 380990.0,
      "end_time": 383990.0,
      "text": "even if it&#39;s consistent with rival theories."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 384704.0,
      "end_time": 387656.0,
      "text": "Data is just a collection of facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 388402.0,
      "end_time": 393325.0,
      "text": "Evidence is data that supports one theory and rules out others."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 394665.0,
      "end_time": 397148.0,
      "text": "So the best way to support your theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 397172.0,
      "end_time": 401102.0,
      "text": "is actually to try to disprove it, to play devil&#39;s advocate."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 401466.0,
      "end_time": 406184.0,
      "text": "So test something, like 4, 12, 26."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 406938.0,
      "end_time": 410621.0,
      "text": "If you got a yes to that, that would disprove your theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 410645.0,
      "end_time": 412580.0,
      "text": "of successive even numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 413232.0,
      "end_time": 415248.0,
      "text": "Yet this test is powerful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 415272.0,
      "end_time": 420117.0,
      "text": "because if you got a no, it would rule out \"any three even numbers\""
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 420141.0,
      "end_time": 421853.0,
      "text": "and \"any three increasing numbers.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 421877.0,
      "end_time": 425218.0,
      "text": "It would rule out the rival theories, but not rule out yours."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 425968.0,
      "end_time": 430762.0,
      "text": "But most people are too afraid of testing the 4, 12, 26,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 430786.0,
      "end_time": 434949.0,
      "text": "because they don&#39;t want to get a yes and prove their pet theory to be wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 436727.0,
      "end_time": 442402.0,
      "text": "Confirmation bias is not only about failing to search for new data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 442427.0,
      "end_time": 445500.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s also about misinterpreting data once you receive it."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 446339.0,
      "end_time": 449887.0,
      "text": "And this applies outside the lab to important, real-world problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 449911.0,
      "end_time": 453220.0,
      "text": "Indeed, Thomas Edison famously said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 453244.0,
      "end_time": 455132.0,
      "text": "\"I have not failed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 455156.0,
      "end_time": 459344.0,
      "text": "I have found 10,000 ways that won&#39;t work.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 460281.0,
      "end_time": 462908.0,
      "text": "Finding out that you&#39;re wrong"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 462932.0,
      "end_time": 465665.0,
      "text": "is the only way to find out what&#39;s right."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 466654.0,
      "end_time": 469600.0,
      "text": "Say you&#39;re a university admissions director"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 469624.0,
      "end_time": 472187.0,
      "text": "and your theory is that only students with good grades"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 472211.0,
      "end_time": 473974.0,
      "text": "from rich families do well."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 474339.0,
      "end_time": 476529.0,
      "text": "So you only let in such students."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 476553.0,
      "end_time": 477703.0,
      "text": "And they do well."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 478482.0,
      "end_time": 481254.0,
      "text": "But that&#39;s also consistent with the rival theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 481593.0,
      "end_time": 484340.0,
      "text": "Perhaps all students with good grades do well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 484364.0,
      "end_time": 485544.0,
      "text": "rich or poor."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 486307.0,
      "end_time": 490370.0,
      "text": "But you never test that theory because you never let in poor students"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 490610.0,
      "end_time": 492861.0,
      "text": "because you don&#39;t want to be proven wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 494577.0,
      "end_time": 496434.0,
      "text": "So, what have we learned?"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 497315.0,
      "end_time": 500875.0,
      "text": "A story is not fact, because it may not be true."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 501498.0,
      "end_time": 503585.0,
      "text": "A fact is not data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 503609.0,
      "end_time": 507647.0,
      "text": "it may not be representative if it&#39;s only one data point."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 508680.0,
      "end_time": 511290.0,
      "text": "And data is not evidence --"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 511530.0,
      "end_time": 514731.0,
      "text": "it may not be supportive if it&#39;s consistent with rival theories."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 516145.0,
      "end_time": 518423.0,
      "text": "So, what do you do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 519464.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522146.00000000006,
      "text": "When you&#39;re at the inflection points of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 522169.0,
      "end_time": 524736.0,
      "text": "deciding on a strategy for your business,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 524760.0,
      "end_time": 527371.0,
      "text": "a parenting technique for your child"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 527395.0,
      "end_time": 529823.0,
      "text": "or a regimen for your health,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 529847.0,
      "end_time": 533386.0,
      "text": "how do you ensure that you don&#39;t have a story"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 533410.0,
      "end_time": 534877.0,
      "text": "but you have evidence?"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 536268.0,
      "end_time": 537887.0,
      "text": "Let me give you three tips."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 538641.0,
      "end_time": 542625.0,
      "text": "The first is to actively seek other viewpoints."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 542649.0,
      "end_time": 546243.0,
      "text": "Read and listen to people you flagrantly disagree with."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 546267.0,
      "end_time": 549755.0,
      "text": "Ninety percent of what they say may be wrong, in your view."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 550728.0,
      "end_time": 552861.0,
      "text": "But what if 10 percent is right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 553851.0,
      "end_time": 555470.0,
      "text": "As Aristotle said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 555494.0,
      "end_time": 557708.0,
      "text": "\"The mark of an educated man"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 557732.0,
      "end_time": 561129.0,
      "text": "is the ability to entertain a thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 561153.0,
      "end_time": 563486.0,
      "text": "without necessarily accepting it.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 564649.0,
      "end_time": 566903.0,
      "text": "Surround yourself with people who challenge you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 566917.0,
      "end_time": 570616.0,
      "text": "and create a culture that actively encourages dissent."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 571347.0,
      "end_time": 573665.0,
      "text": "Some banks suffered from groupthink,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 573689.0,
      "end_time": 577997.0,
      "text": "where staff were too afraid to challenge management&#39;s lending decisions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 578220.0,
      "end_time": 580488.0,
      "text": "contributing to the financial crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 581290.0,
      "end_time": 585228.0,
      "text": "In a meeting, appoint someone to be devil&#39;s advocate"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 585252.0,
      "end_time": 586894.0,
      "text": "against your pet idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 587720.0,
      "end_time": 590291.0,
      "text": "And don&#39;t just hear another viewpoint --"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 590315.0,
      "end_time": 592491.0,
      "text": "listen to it, as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 593389.0,
      "end_time": 595793.0,
      "text": "As psychologist Stephen Covey said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 595817.0,
      "end_time": 599214.0,
      "text": "\"Listen with the intent to understand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 599238.0,
      "end_time": 600904.0,
      "text": "not the intent to reply.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 601642.0,
      "end_time": 605134.0,
      "text": "A dissenting viewpoint is something to learn from"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 605158.0,
      "end_time": 606706.0,
      "text": "not to argue against."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 607690.0,
      "end_time": 611556.0,
      "text": "Which takes us to the other forgotten terms in Bayesian inference."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 612198.0,
      "end_time": 614521.0,
      "text": "Because data allows you to learn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 614546.0,
      "end_time": 618610.0,
      "text": "but learning is only relative to a starting point."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 618850.0,
      "end_time": 623801.0,
      "text": "If you started with complete certainty that your pet theory must be true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 623825.0,
      "end_time": 625722.0,
      "text": "then your view won&#39;t change --"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 625746.0,
      "end_time": 628212.0,
      "text": "regardless of what data you see."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 628641.0,
      "end_time": 633310.0,
      "text": "Only if you are truly open to the possibility of being wrong"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 633560.0,
      "end_time": 634323.0,
      "text": "can you ever learn."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 635580.0,
      "end_time": 637675.0,
      "text": "As Leo Tolstoy wrote,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 637699.0,
      "end_time": 639881.0,
      "text": "\"The most difficult subjects"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 639905.0,
      "end_time": 643400.0,
      "text": "can be explained to the most slow-witted man"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 643640.0,
      "end_time": 645817.0,
      "text": "if he has not formed any idea of them already."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 646365.0,
      "end_time": 648238.0,
      "text": "But the simplest thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 648262.0,
      "end_time": 651333.0,
      "text": "cannot be made clear to the most intelligent man"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 651357.0,
      "end_time": 654690.0,
      "text": "if he is firmly persuaded that he knows already.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 656500.0,
      "end_time": 660243.0,
      "text": "Tip number two is \"listen to experts.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 661400.0,
      "end_time": 664531.0,
      "text": "Now, that&#39;s perhaps the most unpopular advice that I could give you."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 664556.0,
      "end_time": 665776.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 665800.0,
      "end_time": 670538.0,
      "text": "British politician Michael Gove famously said that people in this country"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 670562.0,
      "end_time": 672838.0,
      "text": "have had enough of experts."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 673696.0,
      "end_time": 677204.0,
      "text": "A recent poll showed that more people would trust their hairdresser --"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 677228.0,
      "end_time": 679512.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 679537.0,
      "end_time": 681370.0,
      "text": "or the man on the street"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 681394.0,
      "end_time": 685699.0,
      "text": "than they would leaders of businesses, the health service and even charities."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 686227.0,
      "end_time": 690204.0,
      "text": "So we respect a teeth-whitening formula discovered by a mom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 690228.0,
      "end_time": 693425.0,
      "text": "or we listen to an actress&#39;s view on vaccination."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 693450.0,
      "end_time": 696315.0,
      "text": "We like people who tell it like it is, who go with their gut,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 696339.0,
      "end_time": 698139.0,
      "text": "and we call them authentic."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 698847.0,
      "end_time": 702610.0,
      "text": "But gut feel can only get you so far."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 702736.0,
      "end_time": 707172.0,
      "text": "Gut feel would tell you never to give water to a baby with diarrhea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 707196.0,
      "end_time": 709514.0,
      "text": "because it would just flow out the other end."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 709538.0,
      "end_time": 712116.0,
      "text": "Expertise tells you otherwise."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 713149.0,
      "end_time": 716577.0,
      "text": "You&#39;d never trust your surgery to the man on the street."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 716887.0,
      "end_time": 720473.0,
      "text": "You&#39;d want an expert who spent years doing surgery"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 720498.0,
      "end_time": 722498.0,
      "text": "and knows the best techniques."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 723514.0,
      "end_time": 726647.0,
      "text": "But that should apply to every major decision."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 727255.0,
      "end_time": 731811.0,
      "text": "Politics, business, health advice"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 731835.0,
      "end_time": 734731.0,
      "text": "require expertise, just like surgery."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 736474.0,
      "end_time": 740130.0,
      "text": "So then, why are experts so mistrusted?"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 740981.0,
      "end_time": 744220.0,
      "text": "Well, one reason is they&#39;re seen as out of touch."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 744244.0,
      "end_time": 748334.0,
      "text": "A millionaire CEO couldn&#39;t possibly speak for the man on the street."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 749455.0,
      "end_time": 753140.0,
      "text": "But true expertise is found on evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 753447.0,
      "end_time": 756352.0,
      "text": "And evidence stands up for the man on the street"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 756376.0,
      "end_time": 757909.0,
      "text": "and against the elites."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 758456.0,
      "end_time": 761123.0,
      "text": "Because evidence forces you to prove it."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 761774.0,
      "end_time": 766195.0,
      "text": "Evidence prevents the elites from imposing their own view"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 766219.0,
      "end_time": 767369.0,
      "text": "without proof."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 769600.0,
      "end_time": 771770.0,
      "text": "A second reason why experts are not trusted"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 771101.0,
      "end_time": 774188.0,
      "text": "is that different experts say different things."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 774212.0,
      "end_time": 778688.0,
      "text": "For every expert who claimed that leaving the EU would be bad for Britain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 778712.0,
      "end_time": 781141.0,
      "text": "another expert claimed it would be good."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 781165.0,
      "end_time": 784932.0,
      "text": "Half of these so-called experts will be wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 785774.0,
      "end_time": 790170.0,
      "text": "And I have to admit that most papers written by experts are wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 790520.0,
      "end_time": 794250.0,
      "text": "Or at best, make claims that the evidence doesn&#39;t actually support."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 794990.0,
      "end_time": 798123.0,
      "text": "So we can&#39;t just take an expert&#39;s word for it."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 798776.0,
      "end_time": 804810.0,
      "text": "In November 2016, a study on executive pay hit national headlines."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 805240.0,
      "end_time": 808130.0,
      "text": "Even though none of the newspapers who covered the study"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 808154.0,
      "end_time": 809754.0,
      "text": "had even seen the study."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 810685.0,
      "end_time": 812218.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t even out yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 812708.0,
      "end_time": 814911.0,
      "text": "They just took the author&#39;s word for it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 815768.0,
      "end_time": 817168.0,
      "text": "just like with Belle."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 818930.0,
      "end_time": 820529.0,
      "text": "Nor does it mean that we can just handpick any study"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 820553.0,
      "end_time": 822664.0,
      "text": "that happens to support our viewpoint --"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 822688.0,
      "end_time": 824790.0,
      "text": "that would, again, be confirmation bias."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 824815.0,
      "end_time": 827370.0,
      "text": "Nor does it mean that if seven studies show A"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 827394.0,
      "end_time": 829620.0,
      "text": "and three show B,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 829860.0,
      "end_time": 830569.0,
      "text": "that A must be true."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 831109.0,
      "end_time": 833768.0,
      "text": "What matters is the quality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 833792.0,
      "end_time": 836609.0,
      "text": "and not the quantity of expertise."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 837879.0,
      "end_time": 839679.0,
      "text": "So we should do two things."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 840434.0,
      "end_time": 845120.0,
      "text": "First, we should critically examine the credentials of the authors."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 845807.0,
      "end_time": 849950.0,
      "text": "Just like you&#39;d critically examine the credentials of a potential surgeon."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 850347.0,
      "end_time": 853553.0,
      "text": "Are they truly experts in the matter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 853577.0,
      "end_time": 855844.0,
      "text": "or do they have a vested interest?"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 856768.0,
      "end_time": 859291.0,
      "text": "Second, we should pay particular attention"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 859315.0,
      "end_time": 863204.0,
      "text": "to papers published in the top academic journals."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 864380.0,
      "end_time": 867899.0,
      "text": "Now, academics are often accused of being detached from the real world."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 868585.0,
      "end_time": 872315.0,
      "text": "But this detachment gives you years to spend on a study."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 872339.0,
      "end_time": 874244.0,
      "text": "To really nail down a result,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 874268.0,
      "end_time": 876283.0,
      "text": "to rule out those rival theories,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 876307.0,
      "end_time": 879441.0,
      "text": "and to distinguish correlation from causation."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 880172.0,
      "end_time": 883649.0,
      "text": "And academic journals involve peer review,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 883673.0,
      "end_time": 885967.0,
      "text": "where a paper is rigorously scrutinized"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 885991.0,
      "end_time": 887410.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 887434.0,
      "end_time": 889367.0,
      "text": "by the world&#39;s leading minds."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 890434.0,
      "end_time": 892990.0,
      "text": "The better the journal, the higher the standard."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 893140.0,
      "end_time": 898162.0,
      "text": "The most elite journals reject 95 percent of papers."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 899434.0,
      "end_time": 902766.0,
      "text": "Now, academic evidence is not everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 903109.0,
      "end_time": 905776.0,
      "text": "Real-world experience is critical, also."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 906465.0,
      "end_time": 909865.0,
      "text": "And peer review is not perfect, mistakes are made."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 910530.0,
      "end_time": 912593.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s better to go with something checked"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 912617.0,
      "end_time": 914284.0,
      "text": "than something unchecked."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 914696.0,
      "end_time": 917895.0,
      "text": "If we latch onto a study because we like the findings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 917919.0,
      "end_time": 921807.0,
      "text": "without considering who it&#39;s by or whether it&#39;s even been vetted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 921831.0,
      "end_time": 925458.0,
      "text": "there is a massive chance that that study is misleading."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 926894.0,
      "end_time": 929474.0,
      "text": "And those of us who claim to be experts"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 929498.0,
      "end_time": 932751.0,
      "text": "should recognize the limitations of our analysis."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 933244.0,
      "end_time": 937807.0,
      "text": "Very rarely is it possible to prove or predict something with certainty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 938292.0,
      "end_time": 942661.0,
      "text": "yet it&#39;s so tempting to make a sweeping, unqualified statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 943690.0,
      "end_time": 947413.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s easier to turn into a headline or to be tweeted in 140 characters."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 948417.0,
      "end_time": 951559.0,
      "text": "But even evidence may not be proof."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 952481.0,
      "end_time": 956691.0,
      "text": "It may not be universal, it may not apply in every setting."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 957252.0,
      "end_time": 962171.0,
      "text": "So don&#39;t say, \"Red wine causes longer life,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 962196.0,
      "end_time": 966878.0,
      "text": "when the evidence is only that red wine is correlated with longer life."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 967379.0,
      "end_time": 970149.0,
      "text": "And only then in people who exercise as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 971868.0,
      "end_time": 975834.0,
      "text": "Tip number three is \"pause before sharing anything.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 976907.0,
      "end_time": 980371.0,
      "text": "The Hippocratic oath says, \"First, do no harm.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 981460.0,
      "end_time": 984180.0,
      "text": "What we share is potentially contagious,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 984204.0,
      "end_time": 987887.0,
      "text": "so be very careful about what we spread."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 988632.0,
      "end_time": 991584.0,
      "text": "Our goal should not be to get likes or retweets."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 991609.0,
      "end_time": 995594.0,
      "text": "Otherwise, we only share the consensus; we don&#39;t challenge anyone&#39;s thinking."
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 996850.0,
      "end_time": 998990.0,
      "text": "Otherwise, we only share what sounds good,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 999140.0,
      "end_time": 1001414.0,
      "text": "regardless of whether it&#39;s evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 1002190.0,
      "end_time": 1004656.0,
      "text": "Instead, we should ask the following:"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 1005570.0,
      "end_time": 1007705.0,
      "text": "If it&#39;s a story, is it true?"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 1007730.0,
      "end_time": 1010595.0,
      "text": "If it&#39;s true, is it backed up by large-scale evidence?"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 1010620.0,
      "end_time": 1013215.0,
      "text": "If it is, who is it by, what are their credentials?"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 1013240.0,
      "end_time": 1015996.0,
      "text": "Is it published, how rigorous is the journal?"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 1016730.0,
      "end_time": 1019497.0,
      "text": "And ask yourself the million-dollar question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 1019980.0,
      "end_time": 1024200.0,
      "text": "If the same study was written by the same authors with the same credentials"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 1025130.0000000001,
      "end_time": 1026717.0000000001,
      "text": "but found the opposite results,"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 1027609.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1031302.9999999999,
      "text": "would you still be willing to believe it and to share it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 1033440.0,
      "end_time": 1035686.0,
      "text": "Treating any problem --"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 1035710.0,
      "end_time": 1039501.0,
      "text": "a nation&#39;s economic problem or an individual&#39;s health problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 1039530.0,
      "end_time": 1040680.0,
      "text": "is difficult."
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 1041240.0,
      "end_time": 1045623.0,
      "text": "So we must ensure that we have the very best evidence to guide us."
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 1046190.0,
      "end_time": 1048871.0,
      "text": "Only if it&#39;s true can it be fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 1049600.0,
      "end_time": 1052381.0,
      "text": "Only if it&#39;s representative can it be data."
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 1053130.0,
      "end_time": 1056295.0,
      "text": "Only if it&#39;s supportive can it be evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 1056320.0,
      "end_time": 1061487.0,
      "text": "And only with evidence can we move from a post-truth world"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 1061510.0,
      "end_time": 1063912.0,
      "text": "to a pro-truth world."
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 1064180.0,
      "end_time": 1065514.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 1065540.0,
      "end_time": 1066690.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}